        howitworks_p1: "The calculator compares two economic scenarios for each profession: the <strong>total cost of a human employee</strong> (gross salary plus social contributions, severance pay and insurance, which in Italy add about 30% to the cost) and the <strong>cost of a specialized AI agent</strong> delivered as SaaS (Software as a Service), including the monthly fee and initial implementation cost.",
        howitworks_p2: "For each professional role, the model considers three key variables:",
        howitworks_li1: "<strong>Compared accuracy</strong> — the typical error rate of a human professional versus an AI system on the same task, based on publicly available industry data",
        howitworks_li2: "<strong>Risk factor</strong> — how structured, repeatable and measurable the role is (the more standardized, the more automatable)",
        howitworks_li3: "<strong>Estimated critical year</strong> — a rough projection of when the cost and reliability of AI stably surpass those of a junior/mid-level professional in that specific role",
        howitworks_p3: "The default values (salary, AI cost, accuracy) are fully <strong>editable</strong>: enter your real numbers to get a personalized projection for your specific situation, whether you're an employee wanting to understand your own risk or a company evaluating an automation investment.",
        methodology_title: "Methodology and data sources",
        methodology_p1: "The default salary data comes from public industry sources updated to 2026, including <strong>Glassdoor Italy, Indeed, Jooble, Talent.com</strong> and Crebs' creative/tech salary guide. For each role we cross-referenced multiple sources to get a realistic estimate of average gross annual pay in Italy.",
        methodology_p2: "AI service costs are estimated based on 2026 market prices for comparable tools by category (writing assistants, customer service chatbots, AI-integrated accounting software, business intelligence tools), differentiated by complexity and the level of regulation in the sector.",
        methodology_p3: "<strong>Important:</strong> every estimate shown by the calculator is a simplification for illustrative and educational purposes. The real labor market is influenced by countless factors — regulatory, cultural, sector-specific, geographic — that a single model cannot fully capture. The \"critical year\" projections are reasoned hypotheses, not certain predictions.",
        faq_title: "Frequently asked questions",
        faq_q1: "Will my job definitely be replaced by AI?",
        faq_a1: "No, the calculator shows a risk estimate based on market patterns, not a certainty. It depends heavily on how much you can specialize in tasks that require human judgment, relationships and creativity — areas where AI remains weak even in high-risk roles.",
        faq_q2: "Why do some jobs have a \"critical year\" sooner than others?",
        faq_a2: "Because the speed of AI adoption varies greatly depending on how repetitive and measurable a task is. A translator or accountant perform highly standardized tasks, while a nurse or teacher have relational and physical components that are hard to automate even with very advanced technology.",
        faq_q3: "Can I use the calculator for my business?",
        faq_a3: "Yes. By changing the salary, AI cost and setup values with your real numbers, you can get an approximate estimate of the ROI of potential automation for your specific business case. Remember this is still an indicative estimate, not professional advice.",
        faq_q4: "Is the tool free?",
        faq_a4: "Yes, completely free and no registration required. The site is supported through non-intrusive advertising.",
